          <p>K-Electric (KE) is Pakistan's only privately owned electricity distribution company. Formerly known as Karachi Electric Supply Corporation (KESC), it was privatized in 2005 and rebranded as K-Electric. KE generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to over 3.3 million consumers across Karachi — Pakistan's largest city and commercial capital — plus surrounding areas including Dhabeji, Gharo, Hub, and parts of Lasbela district in Balochistan.</p>
          <p>Unlike all other DISCOs in Pakistan which are government-owned and managed through PITC, K-Electric operates its own independent billing system. This is why KE bills use a <strong>13-digit account number</strong> instead of the 14-digit reference number used by WAPDA DISCOs.</p>
          <p>K-Electric introduced a <strong>new bill format in August 2025</strong> that simplified layout, added a message board section for consumer-specific updates, and improved tariff transparency on the bill face.</p>
